1
00:00:00,248 --> 00:00:04,130
If this movie was aired in our universe, it would have made millions by now.

2
00:00:04,130 --> 00:00:06,450
If it wasn't for you, this movie wouldn't have happened.

3
00:00:06,450 --> 00:00:08,520
It's life to meet and part.

4
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:10,280
I'm so proud to work with you guys.

5
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:12,480
What are you going to do now?

6
00:00:12,480 --> 00:00:14,230
I'm moving back home.

7
00:00:14,230 --> 00:00:19,168
If I stop writing screenplays, I won't be able to cover the rent.

8
00:00:20,760 --> 00:00:25,160
Talay, would you like to move in with me?

9
00:00:41,180 --> 00:00:44,564
Your clothes are colorful.

10
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:48,708
They're making my room a lot livelier.

11
00:00:51,310 --> 00:00:52,810
Wait.

12
00:00:53,940 --> 00:00:56,152
Not my room anymore.

13
00:00:57,460 --> 00:00:59,760
Our room.

14
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:01,543
What are you saying?

15
00:01:01,543 --> 00:01:03,482
I'm getting goosebumps.

16
00:01:04,301 --> 00:01:06,421
You said you would watch a movie.

17
00:01:07,352 --> 00:01:09,460
I am.

18
00:01:09,460 --> 00:01:13,372
I prepared popped rice for you already.

19
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:26,400
Tun!

20
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:28,820
Why don't you eat it normally?

21
00:01:28,820 --> 00:01:31,052
I don't want my hands messy.

22
00:01:31,890 --> 00:01:33,690
Can I borrow yours?

23
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:46,900
My hands are clean.

24
00:01:48,263 --> 00:01:50,540
I won't be the only one with sticky hands.

25
00:01:51,744 --> 00:01:53,444
What?

26
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:18,044
We should stop eating popped rice.

27
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:21,900
Better eat something else.

28
00:02:42,530 --> 00:02:44,790
We should stop watching the movie.

29
00:02:50,540 --> 00:02:52,896
Let's get ready for bed.

30
00:03:24,690 --> 00:03:26,090
Here.

31
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:34,956
Do you know who puts toothpaste on each other's toothbrushes?

32
00:03:35,910 --> 00:03:37,790
Who?

33
00:03:37,790 --> 00:03:40,552
Come on. Think.

34
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:43,100
Anyone.

35
00:03:45,380 --> 00:03:50,530
Who is the last person we see before bed

36
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:54,204
and the first person we see after waking up?

37
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:56,668
Can't be anyone else.

38
00:03:56,668 --> 00:04:00,220
Tun, what are you saying?

39
00:04:02,130 --> 00:04:04,300
Just brush your teeth.

40
00:04:27,140 --> 00:04:28,850
Tun!

41
00:04:28,850 --> 00:04:30,400
Enough.

42
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,780
That latter part doesn't sound right.

43
00:04:33,348 --> 00:04:38,524
Do you want me to live with you or do you want something 18+?

44
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:40,539
Come on.

45
00:04:40,539 --> 00:04:42,843
Anything can happen.

46
00:04:42,843 --> 00:04:45,100
No.

47
00:04:45,100 --> 00:04:48,804
Living together will result in us fighting all the time.

48
00:04:57,270 --> 00:04:59,170
Hey, Tun.

49
00:04:59,170 --> 00:05:03,404
About the rental, I can help you pay.

50
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:06,290
No.

51
00:05:06,290 --> 00:05:11,972
I'd feel bad if you just paid and didn't live there with me.

52
00:05:18,980 --> 00:05:24,388
Besides, the reason I want you to move in with me...

53
00:05:24,388 --> 00:05:29,404
is that I'm feeling a bit lost as I won't get to spend time with you anymore.

54
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:36,040
Seeing you 24/7 is heartwarming.

55
00:05:42,210 --> 00:05:45,316
You should spend time with someone else, too.

56
00:05:45,316 --> 00:05:48,200
You might find your portkey.

57
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:52,000
Don't you want to go back?

58
00:05:53,670 --> 00:05:57,880
[Friend Credits]

59
00:06:03,940 --> 00:06:05,550
[Vice Versa]

60
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:54,020
[Vice Versa]

61
00:06:57,645 --> 00:07:00,820
[Episode 6 - Fire Yellow]

62
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:04,724
I still can't find my portkey.

63
00:07:06,460 --> 00:07:09,484
Damn it! I just want to drink so bad.

64
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:14,947
There, there. Let me give you a warm hug. Spend the night with me.

65
00:07:14,947 --> 00:07:17,450
I'll give you free fried chicken.

66
00:07:17,450 --> 00:07:20,083
That's enough. Come here. Do not take advantage of him.

67
00:07:20,083 --> 00:07:21,800
Come here.

68
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,400
Here.

69
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:25,368
Why stop me?

70
00:07:25,368 --> 00:07:26,460
Sit tight.

71
00:07:26,460 --> 00:07:28,880
I'm pretty lonely these days.

72
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:33,340
Tun has been gone. He doesn't come at all.

73
00:07:33,340 --> 00:07:35,920
Where is Tun, Talay?

74
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:37,810
No idea.

75
00:07:37,810 --> 00:07:41,310
Since we disbanded, I haven't seen him.

76
00:07:41,310 --> 00:07:43,616
He doesn't pick up my calls.

77
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:48,600
I haven't seen him for a week.

78
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:50,152
My heart is shattered.

79
00:07:50,152 --> 00:07:52,150
Too much. It's just a week.

80
00:07:52,150 --> 00:07:53,970
Not just a week.

81
00:07:53,970 --> 00:08:00,150
It's 168 hours or 10,080 minutes or...

82
00:08:00,150 --> 00:08:01,600
Enough.

83
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:03,632
Do you miss him that much?

84
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:05,680
You don't get it.

85
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:10,910
When we miss someone, a minute feels like a year.

86
00:08:10,910 --> 00:08:13,084
Right, Talay?

87
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:16,580
- Me?
- Yes.

88
00:08:16,580 --> 00:08:18,930
You two always stuck together.

89
00:08:18,930 --> 00:08:23,812
If one is missing, the other one can't help but feel a bit empty.

90
00:08:47,430 --> 00:08:49,280
Can you sing for me?

91
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:51,283
I want to hear music from our universe.

92
00:08:51,283 --> 00:08:53,819
Sing it yourself.

93
00:08:55,580 --> 00:08:58,136
I want to hear a song you sing.

94
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:03,040
I'm playing games.

95
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:04,660
Please, Talay.

96
00:09:04,660 --> 00:09:08,527
It can be your favorite song. The one by Paradox.

97
00:09:09,420 --> 00:09:10,470
"Love".

98
00:09:10,470 --> 00:09:14,620
No "Love" now. Let me play this game first.

99
00:09:17,710 --> 00:09:19,836
You're mean.

100
00:09:56,050 --> 00:09:58,888
Yeah! The exams are all over.

101
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:01,420
Right.

102
00:10:01,420 --> 00:10:04,280
Studying for the exams was exhausting.

103
00:10:04,930 --> 00:10:07,824
My agony is finally over.

104
00:10:08,820 --> 00:10:10,610
Are you sure?

105
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:13,710
You can't graduate yet, Tess.

106
00:10:13,710 --> 00:10:15,970
Why can't I?

107
00:10:15,970 --> 00:10:18,227
I have lots of accumulated scores.

108
00:10:18,227 --> 00:10:19,730
I won't get an F.

109
00:10:19,730 --> 00:10:21,480
Not this term's courses.

110
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:23,620
Did you forget you're missing one more course?

111
00:10:23,620 --> 00:10:26,850
Right. You said you didn't want to study too much.

112
00:10:26,850 --> 00:10:29,100
So you didn't enroll in the last English course.

113
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:34,463
You have to study alone now. How lonely!

114
00:10:37,350 --> 00:10:41,050
Right. How lonely.

115
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:49,344
Not counting the days when the people around me slowly disappeared one by one.

116
00:10:50,177 --> 00:10:51,590
So dramatic.

117
00:10:51,590 --> 00:10:54,520
Let's leave. Let him play his music video.

118
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:14,980
Tun?

119
00:11:14,980 --> 00:11:16,760
We saw that you were lonely so we're here to keep you company.

120
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:19,913
We've got some beers. Come one.

121
00:11:23,270 --> 00:11:25,190
Let's drink and watch a movie.

122
00:11:25,190 --> 00:11:26,520
It's a long night tonight.

123
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:28,240
Let's watch the one you made.

124
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:30,440
It just hit the streaming app.

125
00:11:31,490 --> 00:11:32,570
Sure.

126
00:11:32,570 --> 00:11:35,000
[MOST POPULAR: Long Distance Relationship]

127
00:11:41,990 --> 00:11:44,640
I designed the ending scene already.

128
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:47,130
After the lead characters parted,

129
00:11:47,130 --> 00:11:50,570
they run into each other here one day.

130
00:11:51,860 --> 00:11:54,800
It's my first snow in life.

131
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:59,860
That means I'm the first one you've seen snow with.

132
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:08,510
If this movie was aired in our universe, it would have made millions by now.

133
00:12:08,510 --> 00:12:12,880
If it wasn't for you, this movie wouldn't have happened.

134
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:15,870
I'm going to bed.

135
00:12:15,870 --> 00:12:17,570
Drowsy.

136
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:24,440
Hey, Tun.

137
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:57,270
I'm starving, Tess.

138
00:12:57,270 --> 00:12:59,260
Let's go eat.

139
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,600
Wake up.

140
00:13:03,730 --> 00:13:06,760
He's never been a morning person.

141
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:09,824
We must play hardball.

142
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:12,930
Ready?

143
00:13:12,930 --> 00:13:15,680
1, 2, 3.

144
00:13:15,680 --> 00:13:18,412
Tickle. Tickle.

145
00:13:29,490 --> 00:13:31,320
Who are you here for?

146
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:33,244
Is Tun home?

147
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:44,120
He's been like this since he got back.

148
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:48,980
Spending alone time in his room, not associating with anyone.

149
00:13:48,980 --> 00:13:52,180
It's good you're here, Tess. Please deal with him.

150
00:13:56,220 --> 00:13:57,720
Hey, Tun.

151
00:14:09,620 --> 00:14:11,220
Talay.

152
00:14:12,352 --> 00:14:13,780
What brought you here?

153
00:14:13,780 --> 00:14:18,580
It hasn't even been that long, but you look a lot older.

154
00:14:18,580 --> 00:14:20,648
Your ears are deaf.

155
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:25,013
And look. Your mustache has turned white.

156
00:14:31,060 --> 00:14:32,440
Yeah.

157
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:34,436
Now you're as old as me.

158
00:14:41,350 --> 00:14:43,288
What are you listening to?

159
00:14:45,032 --> 00:14:46,400
Some music.

160
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:51,388
But I don't know any of the songs in this universe.

161
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:55,270
♪ Oh dear love ♪

162
00:14:55,270 --> 00:14:58,173
♪ Please look at me ♪

163
00:14:58,173 --> 00:15:06,760
♪ Sometimes we meet on a heartbreaking day ♪

164
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:15,170
♪ You come in and embrace me softly ♪

165
00:15:15,170 --> 00:15:18,040
♪ Oh dear love ♪

166
00:15:18,040 --> 00:15:20,880
♪ Sweet love ♪

167
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:29,080
♪ You're a beauty, my heart gets carried away ♪

168
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:31,928
♪ Look at you ♪

169
00:15:31,928 --> 00:15:34,600
♪ Where are you? ♪

170
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:39,548
♪ Oh dear love, I want to meet you ♪

171
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:46,260
♪ You can do anything ♪

172
00:15:46,260 --> 00:15:53,356
♪ Oh dear love, I love you ♪

173
00:16:00,428 --> 00:16:05,120
The song you wanted to hear. I played it.

174
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,100
I should leave now.

175
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:14,260
You came all the way here just to play me that song?

176
00:16:14,260 --> 00:16:16,948
You've been gone for 9 days.

177
00:16:16,948 --> 00:16:22,700
Do you have any idea how long that 12,960 minutes I waited for you

178
00:16:22,700 --> 00:16:24,870
felt like?

179
00:16:27,160 --> 00:16:30,860
Tun, I...

180
00:16:32,980 --> 00:16:35,420
I freaking missed you.

181
00:16:38,390 --> 00:16:39,990
I know.

182
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:43,160
Because for me,

183
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:49,208
it was 777,600 seconds that I spent missing you like crazy, too.

184
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:22,260
I have a question.

185
00:17:22,260 --> 00:17:24,876
Why did you disappear?

186
00:17:25,340 --> 00:17:27,672
I don't have much money left.

187
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:31,400
And I don't want to bother Pakorn's parents.

188
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:35,596
I tried to save money as much as I could.

189
00:17:36,220 --> 00:17:38,370
I stayed in.

190
00:17:38,370 --> 00:17:42,640
I didn't contact anyone. I didn't go anywhere.

191
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:44,460
I only ate at home.

192
00:17:44,460 --> 00:17:46,572
Is it that bad?

193
00:17:48,050 --> 00:17:52,652
Then, why didn't you answer my calls?

194
00:17:53,220 --> 00:17:56,210
Because if you said you wanted to see me

195
00:17:56,210 --> 00:18:00,480
or if I heard your voice,

196
00:18:01,590 --> 00:18:05,776
I wouldn't be able to resist going to see you, Talay.

197
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:16,380
I tried to find a new job,

198
00:18:16,380 --> 00:18:19,420
but there was no job I wanted to do.

199
00:18:19,420 --> 00:18:21,140
Why not?

200
00:18:22,020 --> 00:18:24,100
Because you were not part of it.

201
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:29,830
A life of doing things alone...

202
00:18:31,340 --> 00:18:33,260
is not fun at all.

203
00:18:36,797 --> 00:18:38,090
I think we...

204
00:18:38,090 --> 00:18:40,057
Tun. Tess.

205
00:18:40,057 --> 00:18:43,880
I prepared you guys some snacks. Come have some.

206
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:45,777
Yes, Mom.

207
00:18:45,777 --> 00:18:47,020
Hello, Dad.

208
00:18:47,020 --> 00:18:48,080
Hello.

209
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:50,532
Glad to finally meet you in person, Tess.

210
00:18:50,532 --> 00:18:54,450
Ever since Tun got home, he hasn't talked about anything.

211
00:18:54,450 --> 00:18:55,749
He seems to forget everything.

212
00:18:55,749 --> 00:18:57,920
He only talked about one thing. You, Tess.

213
00:18:57,920 --> 00:19:01,812
Really, Dad? Did he gossip about me?

214
00:19:02,530 --> 00:19:05,500
No. He mainly said you're great.

215
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:07,560
You're so helpful. Like when he was put in jail...

216
00:19:07,560 --> 00:19:09,520
Dad!

217
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:11,080
That's enough.

218
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:13,420
Have you eaten anything yet, Tess?

219
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:16,140
Can I make you anything? You guys can eat together.

220
00:19:16,140 --> 00:19:18,360
Thank you, Mom. I'm hungry.

221
00:19:18,360 --> 00:19:21,440
Okay then. Just one second.

222
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:24,624
Honey, come help me. Let the kids talk. Come here.

223
00:19:24,624 --> 00:19:27,470
- Of course.
- Chop-chop.

224
00:19:29,170 --> 00:19:31,200
Pakorn's parents are lovely.

225
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:34,180
I guess this is such a warm family.

226
00:19:34,180 --> 00:19:35,680
So lovely.

227
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:39,170
They always give Pakorn the things he likes.

228
00:19:39,170 --> 00:19:42,896
Here. Fill your stomach first.

229
00:19:46,180 --> 00:19:48,936
Pakorn must like this very much.

230
00:19:58,904 --> 00:20:00,844
I like it, too.

231
00:20:04,990 --> 00:20:06,790
I mean you.

232
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:11,800
What are you saying?

233
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:14,190
I like when you eat.

234
00:20:14,190 --> 00:20:17,640
You make everything look so yummy.

235
00:20:19,550 --> 00:20:22,156
Then I'll eat them all by myself.

236
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:32,450
Who is it?

237
00:20:32,450 --> 00:20:34,620
I'll go get the door.

238
00:20:34,620 --> 00:20:37,640
Don't bother. I just invited myself in.

239
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:39,670
I come to this house often.

240
00:20:39,670 --> 00:20:41,840
How have you been? I missed you guys.

241
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:44,040
I brought you guys northern Thai sausages.

242
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:46,610
Up! What brings you here?

243
00:20:46,610 --> 00:20:48,460
I missed your foul mouth so bad.

244
00:20:48,460 --> 00:20:50,950
I know. I'm so proud of it.

245
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:53,420
Now that we're here, should we call Aou?

246
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:55,823
- Do it.
- Go ahead, Tess.

247
00:21:00,710 --> 00:21:02,620
Hi, Aou.

248
00:21:02,620 --> 00:21:04,890
Hello. Hello.

249
00:21:04,890 --> 00:21:08,940
What did you say? I have no reception.

250
00:21:08,940 --> 00:21:11,248
Hello. Hello.

251
00:21:11,248 --> 00:21:15,477
He's probably fishing. He said he had no reception.

252
00:21:15,477 --> 00:21:17,550
Uh... okay. I just got my reception.

253
00:21:17,550 --> 00:21:20,232
It's nice and clear now.

254
00:21:20,232 --> 00:21:22,870
- Aou!
- You and you and you!

255
00:21:27,700 --> 00:21:30,830
Hold on. I'm lost.

256
00:21:30,830 --> 00:21:32,350
Is this destiny?

257
00:21:32,350 --> 00:21:34,390
There's no such a thing.

258
00:21:34,390 --> 00:21:36,560
I destined this.

259
00:21:36,560 --> 00:21:39,830
After you came, I called them here too.

260
00:21:39,830 --> 00:21:42,130
Luckily, they were in Bangkok.

261
00:21:42,130 --> 00:21:44,456
I freaking missed you guys.

262
00:21:45,360 --> 00:21:46,860
Guys.

263
00:21:47,860 --> 00:21:53,380
Friend Credits!

264
00:21:53,380 --> 00:21:56,220
I missed this so bad. Haven't done it in a long time.

265
00:21:56,220 --> 00:21:58,417
But first,

266
00:21:58,417 --> 00:22:00,240
I need something to eat.

267
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:01,540
Stop.

268
00:22:01,540 --> 00:22:03,732
You can't eat these.

269
00:22:05,770 --> 00:22:08,160
They've been reserved.

270
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,620
He said he would eat them all by himself.

271
00:22:22,950 --> 00:22:24,520
No way.

272
00:22:24,520 --> 00:22:26,500
Stop! Stop.

273
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:28,912
Nobody can have them.

274
00:22:29,510 --> 00:22:31,310
Fine.

275
00:22:34,550 --> 00:22:38,172
Friend Credits!

276
00:22:43,654 --> 00:22:46,951
