What do you think we traveled between universes to learn?

551
00:41:51,060 --> 00:41:52,760
No idea.

552
00:41:53,890 --> 00:41:58,196
Perhaps if we stay a little longer, we'll find out.

553
00:42:02,850 --> 00:42:04,492
Maybe...

554
00:42:05,650 --> 00:42:07,500
Maybe?

555
00:42:07,500 --> 00:42:12,460
I traveled between universes just to meet you.

556
00:42:13,800 --> 00:42:15,200
What?

557
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:16,560
Think about it.

558
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:18,880
If we didn't travel here,

559
00:42:18,880 --> 00:42:22,340
we wouldn't be eating fried chicken together now.

560
00:42:22,340 --> 00:42:23,890
Duh!

561
00:42:23,890 --> 00:42:28,292
Fried chicken is what I eat in whichever universe.

562
00:42:30,380 --> 00:42:35,516
Here. Take a photo and send it to Joobjang to say thanks.

563
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:43,170
Come on.

564
00:42:43,170 --> 00:42:45,190
Look at your face.

565
00:42:45,190 --> 00:42:46,790
Smile.

566
00:42:46,790 --> 00:42:48,780
A happy smile.

567
00:42:50,320 --> 00:42:52,020
Like this?

568
00:42:54,070 --> 00:42:57,556
That smile doesn't say you enjoy the food.

569
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:03,088
It says you're cute.

570
00:43:06,530 --> 00:43:08,936
What should I do then?

571
00:43:08,936 --> 00:43:10,600
Tell me.

572
00:43:11,410 --> 00:43:14,304
Here. Let me help.

573
00:43:15,270 --> 00:43:17,390
Hold the chicken.

574
00:43:17,390 --> 00:43:19,580
Smile widely.

575
00:43:19,580 --> 00:43:22,020
Smiley eyes.

576
00:43:22,020 --> 00:43:24,790
Yes. Chicken closer.

577
00:43:24,790 --> 00:43:26,860
Okay.

578
00:43:27,750 --> 00:43:29,250
I know it.

579
00:43:34,850 --> 00:43:37,250
Smile.

580
00:43:37,250 --> 00:43:38,420
Smile widely.

581
00:43:38,420 --> 00:43:41,248
1, 2, 3.

582
00:43:47,510 --> 00:43:50,050
That's the happy face.

583
00:43:50,050 --> 00:43:52,252
Your eyes dazzle.

584
00:43:52,740 --> 00:43:57,504
I don't know if it's because of the chicken or me.

585
00:44:14,320 --> 00:44:16,512
You didn't wait for me.

586
00:44:18,504 --> 00:44:20,480
You keep talking and talking.

587
00:44:20,480 --> 00:44:22,280
I'm hungry.

588
00:44:24,880 --> 00:44:26,380
Here.

589
00:44:29,700 --> 00:44:31,200
Hold it.

590
00:44:42,370 --> 00:44:44,456
Yes, Dol?

591
00:44:48,820 --> 00:44:50,520
What?

592
00:45:19,360 --> 00:45:24,300
Joob suddenly had a heart attack and passed.

593
00:45:24,300 --> 00:45:27,090
She had no history of heart disease.

594
00:45:27,090 --> 00:45:29,880
How did it happen then?

595
00:45:30,690 --> 00:45:33,300
This symptom has been proven.

596
00:45:34,550 --> 00:45:41,280
It should be that the person in her body in the other universe died.

597
00:45:41,280 --> 00:45:44,350
So Joob died, too.

598
00:45:44,350 --> 00:45:48,640
It's normal for universal travelers.

599
00:45:48,640 --> 00:45:54,160
No matter how many of us have passed, I never get used to it.

600
00:45:54,877 --> 00:45:57,020
I get you.

601
00:45:57,020 --> 00:46:02,520
Joob always said nothing in life was certain.

602
00:46:03,720 --> 00:46:07,228
Whatever I want to do, do it now.

603
00:46:08,440 --> 00:46:10,872
But I never succeeded in doing it.

604
00:46:12,632 --> 00:46:16,270
What do you want to do?

605
00:46:16,270 --> 00:46:18,508
Tell Joob I love her.

606
00:46:22,050 --> 00:46:24,350
I was too afraid to say it.

607
00:46:24,350 --> 00:46:26,850
I thought I had all the time I needed.

608
00:46:26,850 --> 00:46:29,876
She didn't know I liked her.

609
00:46:31,140 --> 00:46:35,160
She had no idea how much I wanted her to be my portkey.

610
00:46:51,760 --> 00:46:55,040
Okay. Let's cut to the last part.

611
00:46:55,040 --> 00:46:58,090
Joob, you talk and end the video.

612
00:46:58,090 --> 00:46:59,690
Okay.

613
00:47:01,551 --> 00:47:05,520
To all universal travelers.

614
00:47:05,520 --> 00:47:08,212
It is going to be tough at the beginning.

615
00:47:08,212 --> 00:47:10,060
Don't get discouraged yet.

616
00:47:10,060 --> 00:47:12,910
Because you're not alone.

617
00:47:12,910 --> 00:47:15,270
I do believe

618
00:47:15,270 --> 00:47:20,360
universal traveling happens for a reason.

619
00:47:21,460 --> 00:47:24,990
Maybe it's a lesson for us

620
00:47:24,990 --> 00:47:27,880
to learn something we're missing.

621
00:47:32,900 --> 00:47:35,180
I stand with every one of you.

622
00:47:37,160 --> 00:47:40,062
[End of video]

623
00:47:44,306 --> 00:47:45,820
Tun.

624
00:47:51,020 --> 00:47:54,998
Will you spend tonight with me?

625
00:48:05,680 --> 00:48:07,380
Are you sleeping?

626
00:48:09,910 --> 00:48:11,610
No.

627
00:48:12,790 --> 00:48:17,496
Aren't you going to ask why I asked you to stay over?

628
00:48:19,136 --> 00:48:21,839
Because you're sad about Joob.

629
00:48:23,750 --> 00:48:25,656
Partly, yes.

630
00:48:26,360 --> 00:48:29,572
I'm starting to be scared of death.

631
00:48:30,340 --> 00:48:35,730
Life is so damn uncertain.

632
00:48:35,730 --> 00:48:39,650
I'm afraid that one day I'll wake up

633
00:48:39,650 --> 00:48:43,310
and people around me will disappear on me.

634
00:48:43,310 --> 00:48:45,362
You're over-thinking it.

635
00:48:51,970 --> 00:48:54,620
What I fear the most...

636
00:48:56,760 --> 00:49:00,300
is that it happens to someone I care about.

637
00:49:05,860 --> 00:49:07,932
Especially, you.

638
00:49:32,910 --> 00:49:36,248
I promise I won't go anywhere.

639
00:49:36,248 --> 00:49:38,428
Nothing will happen to me.

640
00:49:39,520 --> 00:49:43,220
Someone like me doesn't die so easily.

641
00:49:50,800 --> 00:49:53,460
Thank you so much.

642
00:50:06,390 --> 00:50:10,152
There are many things I want to do before I die.

643
00:50:10,900 --> 00:50:13,390
But now,

644
00:50:13,390 --> 00:50:16,504
there's one thing I want to do the most.

645
00:50:20,390 --> 00:50:21,890
What?

646
00:50:22,880 --> 00:50:25,996
Can I hug you to sleep all night tonight?

647
00:50:42,490 --> 00:50:44,590
Good night.

648
00:51:07,680 --> 00:51:11,730
What are you doing? You look like you're going on a date.

649
00:51:11,730 --> 00:51:15,150
I love it when you sing.

650
00:51:15,150 --> 00:51:16,663
That's my t-shirt.

651
00:51:16,663 --> 00:51:18,690
Well, it smells good.

652
00:51:18,690 --> 00:51:21,410
I won't let you go back alone.

653
00:51:21,410 --> 00:51:24,040
Because I'll find my portkey, too.

654
00:51:24,040 --> 00:51:28,238
Hasn't it ever occurred to you that I'm your portkey?

655
00:51:29,030 --> 00:51:32,835
This time, I can kiss you, can't I?

656
00:51:53,250 --> 00:51:58,420
♫ Is it you? That will change this world ♫

657
00:51:58,420 --> 00:52:03,390
♫ Is it you? The person I've been searching a long time for ♫

658
00:52:03,390 --> 00:52:05,970
♫ Have I found, Have I found ♫

659
00:52:06,000 --> 00:52:13,700
♫ Someone who will be ready to walk through this side by side with me from now on ♫

660
00:52:13,710 --> 00:52:18,900
♫ Is it you? That won't let me be sad ♫

661
00:52:18,900 --> 00:52:24,840
♫ After a night of nightmares, making every tomorrow look bright ♫

662
00:52:24,840 --> 00:52:31,500
♫ Forever, please tell me to be confident ♫

663
00:52:31,500 --> 00:52:34,760
♫ That you won't go and leave me ♫
